CAIRO - The United States is looking to reboot its bilateral relations with Egypt as Egyptian President Abdul Fattah al-Sisi meets with his American counterpart Donald Trump.Al-Sisi will visit the White House for the first time since he led the military coup which toppled Mohammed Morsi in 2013.READ: Blind sheikh buried in Egypt after dying in US jailRelations between the long-time allies have been strained since the coup.US officials say Trump is keen to resuscitate their relationship.Egypt receives $1,3-billion in military aid annually.eNCA